==English==

===Etymology===
[[euphemism|Euphemistically]] identifies the purpose of a [[lavatory]] as a place to apply [[makeup|make-up]].

===Verb===
'''to [[powder]] [[one's]] [[nose]]''' 

# {{euphemistic}} To use the [[toilet]] (nearly always refers to women only).
#: ''I'll be right back; I just have to '''powder my nose'''''.
# (of a woman or group of women) To temporarily leave the company of others, often to a [[restroom]], for a brief respite from a crowd, to engage in private conversation, reapply make-up, etc.
#: ''C'mon girls; let's go '''powder our noses'''''.

